<br>
BTW, their names were Rikath and Rovas (the third was a cleric, who I won't name becuase she stayed out of it, and even healed me a few times), and they used incessant foul language, the entire time. Chased off the poor pally I was grouped with, who only wanted his ghoulbane piece.<br>
<br>
Basically, the bottom line is PNP doesn't respect camps, but the unofficial etiquette is one group, one camp, and in the case of these TOFS guys (the original post), they should have respected your camp. It's a good way to get blacklisted, if you frequently ks someone's mobs, or hog multiple camps.<br>
<br>
My experience with TOFS is that each floor is considered a camp. Poeple usually wait for the group in front of them to move up, or if they have keys, go on to the next floor. <p>Xaanru <br>
47th lvl cleric of Mith Marr <br>
