Rodcet Nife <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uiumunorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IumunoRN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowls at you rdy to attack!</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(6/6/02 3:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does our server handle TFS floors</span><hr size=1> first in first served is pretty much the unofficial etiquette.  The PnP rules don't enforce that though.<br>
<br>
There's not much you can do about it except remember the names.<br>
<br>
Though what I did a few times after people barged in my camp, is stop killing anything and withdraw in a safe spot if I was pretty sure they couldn't hold the camp and were just leeching off my efforts at breaking and holding the camp. It's not really &quot;nice&quot; but it's passive and effective.<br>
